  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Coordinated Humanitarian Assistance to Climate and Conflict Affected Populations in Somalia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IOM is coordinating a multi-sector humanitarian response in Somalia. Activities under this project include: (1) the continuation of Displacement Tracking Matrix, including mobility tracking and flow monitoring; (2) camp coordination and camp management (CCCM) activities in the form of site level coordination, supporting communication with communities, strengthening governance systems, CCCM cluster coordination and local capacity building. In addition, IOM is strengthening existing, life-saving humanitarian assistance and scale-up activities in areas where there has been a significant influx of internally displaced persons in the areas of health and water, sanitation and hygiene.</narrative>
  </description>
